1
00:00:00,080 --> 00:00:02,080
Hey, you punk!

2
00:00:02,080 --> 00:00:04,160
Don't mess with my students.

3
00:00:04,160 --> 00:00:05,460
What?

4
00:00:05,460 --> 00:00:07,296
What are you talking about?

5
00:00:07,296 --> 00:00:12,779
I said, do not mess with my students.

6
00:00:12,779 --> 00:00:16,480
<i> [The Witch Store]</i>

7
00:00:16,480 --> 00:00:17,620
♫ <i> Until you apologize </i> ♫

8
00:00:17,620 --> 00:00:21,540
<i> [Episode 9] 
 [When Life Doesn't Go Your Way]</i>

9
00:00:26,960 --> 00:00:28,796
Hey, stop.

10
00:00:28,796 --> 00:00:30,000
Where's your uniform?

11
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:31,236
I am sorry.

12
00:00:31,236 --> 00:00:32,980
Stand here.

13
00:00:34,600 --> 00:00:36,860
Where are you going? Where?

14
00:00:37,700 --> 00:00:40,500
Do you think it's okay for a student not to wear their uniform?

15
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:44,056
Wait.

16
00:00:44,056 --> 00:00:46,376
That isn't the school uniform, right?

17
00:00:46,376 --> 00:00:48,920
I don't have a uniform.

18
00:00:48,920 --> 00:00:51,160
I'm sorry. Go.

19
00:00:54,020 --> 00:00:55,780
Hey, student.

20
00:00:55,780 --> 00:00:57,816
You shouldn't wear slippers to school.

21
00:00:57,816 --> 00:01:00,360
I left my shoes in the classroom.

22
00:01:00,360 --> 00:01:02,356
Then put on your shoes as soon as you get to the classroom.

23
00:01:02,356 --> 00:01:03,640
Yes.

24
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:08,220
Mr. Kim.

25
00:01:08,220 --> 00:01:10,720
Aren't you being too easy on them?

26
00:01:10,720 --> 00:01:13,500
It's because they all have their reasons.

27
00:01:13,500 --> 00:01:18,099
The students aren't scared of you because you're soft like that.

28
00:01:18,760 --> 00:01:22,200
This is just the way I am.

29
00:01:26,560 --> 00:01:28,300
Hey, you come here.

30
00:01:29,040 --> 00:01:32,940
<i> Am I doing the right thing?</i>

31
00:01:33,820 --> 00:01:36,176
The Potsdam Declaration of 1945.

32
00:01:36,176 --> 00:01:39,740
It would be good for us to memorize these three well.

33
00:01:39,740 --> 00:01:42,019
Oh, and for the final exam...

34
00:01:42,019 --> 00:01:45,160
All topics until the building of the Korean government-in-exile will be included in the exam.

35
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:50,060
Taeil, would you wake the students in front of you up?

36
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:54,776
Hey. Hey.

37
00:01:54,776 --> 00:01:56,300
Hey.

38
00:01:59,480 --> 00:02:01,940
They must be really tired.

39
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:05,420
<i> Get up.</i>

40
00:02:05,420 --> 00:02:08,360
Who is sleeping in class?

41
00:02:20,200 --> 00:02:22,479
Okay. That's it for today.

42
00:02:22,479 --> 00:02:24,700
Good work, everyone.

43
00:02:30,200 --> 00:02:32,560
Hey, don't run. It's dangerous.

44
00:02:34,900 --> 00:02:36,700
You two must not have respect.

45
00:02:36,700 --> 00:02:38,139
Should I make you run until you can't run anymore?

46
00:02:38,139 --> 00:02:39,380
<i> I'm sorry, Sir.</i>

47
00:02:39,380 --> 00:02:42,100
- Don't run. 
 - Yes, Sir.

48
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:50,940
<i> I am not doing the wrong thing.</i>

49
00:02:57,300 --> 00:03:01,060
Mr. Kim. What's the matter?

50
00:03:01,060 --> 00:03:03,100
You look...

51
00:03:03,100 --> 00:03:05,076
No, I'm fine.

52
00:03:05,076 --> 00:03:07,560
Then, why are you drinking so much?

53
00:03:11,320 --> 00:03:14,160
- It's the kids, right? 
 - What's up with the kids?

54
00:03:14,160 --> 00:03:17,340
If they don't listen to you, just be tough.

55
00:03:17,340 --> 00:03:19,896
Oh... That's the problem?

56
00:03:19,896 --> 00:03:22,840
Right. You're so soft.

57
00:03:22,840 --> 00:03:25,159
No. They are good kids. It's just...

58
00:03:25,159 --> 00:03:28,160
I know you're a nice guy.

59
00:03:28,160 --> 00:03:31,880
But sometimes, you're so frustrating.

60
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:38,200
Hey. If you want to teach them, you should toughen yourself up.

61
00:03:38,200 --> 00:03:39,980
Is that so?

62
00:03:41,940 --> 00:03:43,960
Let's drink.

63
00:03:50,480 --> 00:03:52,260
<i> Cheers.</i>

64
00:03:56,260 --> 00:03:58,979
♪ I am a fool who loves you ♪

65
00:03:58,979 --> 00:04:00,440
♪ I am a fool... ♪

66
00:04:00,440 --> 00:04:03,459
♪ I am a leech for you ♪

67
00:04:03,459 --> 00:04:05,600
♪ I'm nothing ♪

68
00:04:08,420 --> 00:04:10,420
Shall we have one more drink?

69
00:04:28,760 --> 00:04:31,560
Huh? Teacher.

70
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:34,340
Yes?

71
00:04:34,340 --> 00:04:36,160
Do you know me?

72
00:04:36,160 --> 00:04:37,380
Wow.

73
00:04:37,380 --> 00:04:39,819
You look exactly like my student.

74
00:04:39,819 --> 00:04:42,220
The smart and diligent Hyeji.

75
00:04:42,220 --> 00:04:45,000
Are you okay?

76
00:04:46,060 --> 00:04:49,420
Oh, I lost to alcohol.

77
00:04:49,420 --> 00:04:51,620
I always lose.

78
00:04:51,620 --> 00:04:53,760
I lose to my students.

79
00:04:54,760 --> 00:04:57,520
What's wrong with me?

80
00:04:57,520 --> 00:04:59,880
What should I do?

81
00:05:00,620 --> 00:05:02,330
I mean...

82
00:05:02,330 --> 00:05:06,680
Well, it's because you didn't use this item.

83
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:10,180
Who are you?

84
00:05:14,700 --> 00:05:16,360
What is this?

85
00:05:16,360 --> 00:05:18,040
It's a hat.

86
00:05:18,040 --> 00:05:19,340
"Hat."

87
00:05:19,340 --> 00:05:22,320
It's a magic hat that can change your life.

88
00:05:22,320 --> 00:05:24,140
This will?

89
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:29,340
But isn't it too much?

90
00:05:29,340 --> 00:05:31,599
Kids like things like this.

91
00:05:31,599 --> 00:05:33,760
How tacky.

92
00:05:36,580 --> 00:05:39,240
I enjoy using items like this.

93
00:05:39,240 --> 00:05:42,180
Thank you for the hat.

94
00:05:42,180 --> 00:05:43,380
Good bye.

95
00:05:43,380 --> 00:05:45,160
Wait.

96
00:05:45,160 --> 00:05:47,680
You didn't pay for it.

97
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:49,220
Yeah.

98
00:05:49,220 --> 00:05:51,220
Right.

99
00:05:51,220 --> 00:05:52,740
Here you are.

100
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:55,040
Right.

101
00:05:56,700 --> 00:05:59,040
A three-month installment...

102
00:06:05,580 --> 00:06:07,460
Mr. Kim.

103
00:06:08,340 --> 00:06:09,679
What is that?

104
00:06:09,679 --> 00:06:12,560
This? I bought it.

105
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:14,879
I heard that kids like it.

106
00:06:14,879 --> 00:06:16,660
Is that not the case?

107
00:06:18,200 --> 00:06:20,040
Yes. It's...

108
00:06:20,040 --> 00:06:21,860
Well, it is trendy.

109
00:06:21,860 --> 00:06:23,159
- Really? 
 - Yes.

110
00:06:23,159 --> 00:06:25,020
Thank you.

111
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:32,940
Hey, wait.

112
00:06:32,940 --> 00:06:36,320
I told you I don't have school uniform.

113
00:06:36,320 --> 00:06:39,239
I'm sorry! I'll hurry home and change.

114
00:06:39,239 --> 00:06:41,100
I'm sorry, Sir!

115
00:06:42,080 --> 00:06:43,820
<i> Huh?</i>

116
00:06:43,820 --> 00:06:45,800
<i> What was that?</i>

117
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:47,720
<i> Why did she...</i>

118
00:06:49,900 --> 00:06:52,940
<i>It's a magic hat that can change your life.</i>

119
00:06:52,940 --> 00:06:54,239
<i> Maybe...</i>

120
00:06:54,239 --> 00:06:56,100
<i> This hat?</i>

121
00:07:00,080 --> 00:07:02,760
You shouldn't be running in the hallway.

122
00:07:03,600 --> 00:07:06,019
<i>I'm sorry, Sir! I'm sorry.</i>

123
00:07:06,019 --> 00:07:09,000
<i>I'm sorry. I'm sorry.</i>

124
00:07:15,620 --> 00:07:17,500
<i> I can't believe it.</i>

125
00:07:19,520 --> 00:07:22,140
<i> No. It's true.</i>

126
00:07:22,140 --> 00:07:24,040
<i> It's because of this hat.</i>

127
00:07:31,460 --> 00:07:34,220
<i> It actually works.</i>

128
00:07:34,220 --> 00:07:36,580
<i> It was not a dream.</i>

129
00:07:36,580 --> 00:07:38,260
<i> Epic.</i>

130
00:07:41,260 --> 00:07:44,556
<i> Huh? Isn't it Youngji and Sungwoo?</i>

131
00:07:45,580 --> 00:07:47,239
Tell me again.

132
00:07:47,239 --> 00:07:48,996
I just can't understand.

133
00:07:48,996 --> 00:07:51,140
<i> Who is that guy?</i>

134
00:07:51,140 --> 00:07:52,476
<i> I should help them.</i>

135
00:07:52,476 --> 00:07:54,359
I a'm a stranger here.

136
00:07:54,359 --> 00:07:56,260
Do you know where the convenience store is?

137
00:07:56,260 --> 00:07:58,280
Hey, you punk!

138
00:07:58,280 --> 00:08:00,159
Don't mess with my students!

139
00:08:00,159 --> 00:08:01,539
Excuse me?

140
00:08:01,539 --> 00:08:03,500
What are you talking about?

141
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:07,279
I said don't mess with my students.

142
00:08:07,279 --> 00:08:10,200
Oh, I'm sorry.

143
00:08:14,460 --> 00:08:16,240
Are you okay?

144
00:08:16,240 --> 00:08:19,480
Oh... Yes.

145
00:08:19,480 --> 00:08:21,079
What a relief.

146
00:08:21,079 --> 00:08:23,600
You almost got into trouble.

147
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:29,160
But... where's the hat?

148
00:08:29,160 --> 00:08:31,536
The hat that you were wearing all along at school.

149
00:08:31,536 --> 00:08:33,220
Of course, it's on my head.

150
00:08:33,780 --> 00:08:35,080
What?

151
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:36,520
What?

152
00:08:38,800 --> 00:08:39,896
Where is it?

153
00:08:39,896 --> 00:08:43,400
Thanks, anyways.

154
00:08:43,400 --> 00:08:46,240
You're so cool today.

155
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:49,340
Oh... Well...

156
00:08:50,880 --> 00:08:53,140
Thank you, Sir.

157
00:08:54,380 --> 00:08:56,616
It's nothing.

158
00:08:56,616 --> 00:09:00,019
As your teacher, I did what I should do.

159
00:09:01,280 --> 00:09:02,516
You're cool.

160
00:09:02,516 --> 00:09:05,840
Well, do not say that.

161
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:08,000
Gosh.

162
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:09,200
Was I cool?

163
00:09:09,200 --> 00:09:10,260
Yes.

164
00:09:10,260 --> 00:09:11,900
Totally.

165
00:09:13,060 --> 00:09:15,420
Where is the convenience store?

166
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:21,600
Excuse me. Do you know where the convenience store is?

167
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:23,339
It's near the subway station.

168
00:09:23,339 --> 00:09:24,960
Thanks.

169
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:27,960
Let's go, Hyeji.

170
00:09:39,080 --> 00:09:41,920
By the way, don't you think our teacher acted weird today?

171
00:09:41,920 --> 00:09:44,016
Why? Wasn't he the same as always?

172
00:09:44,016 --> 00:09:46,160
It's just...

173
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:47,836
His hat was really unique.

174
00:09:47,836 --> 00:09:52,240
Really? I thought it was cool.

175
00:09:52,240 --> 00:09:55,800
♫ <i> Because it's the first time </i> ♫

176
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:59,370
♫ <i> It was good back then. Do you remember? </i> ♫

177
00:09:59,370 --> 00:10:05,060
<i> [Confidence Hat]</i>
